newsitem.title: USA: NYMEX ACCESS energy prices up in range-bound trade.
newsitem.headline: NYMEX ACCESS energy prices up in range-bound trade.

text.p: U.S. energy futures prices rose slightly in thin range-bound trade during ACCESS, with sellers assessing the market higher amid news that Iraqi leader Saddam Hussein's son was wounded by gunfire Thursday.
After-hours, January crude gained 13 cents to $23.85 a barrel, as 450 lots traded in the front-month with 890 exchanged overall.
About 122 lots of January heating oil traded, with 230 changing hands in all months as the contract climbed 0.53 cents a gallon to 69.20 cents a gallon.
Front-month gasoline increased to 65.20 cents a gallon, up 0.58 cents as 122 lots changed hands.
